main event: An unidentified bright, white, saucer-shaped object was observed maneuvering over the ocean near Carmel, Washington at around 2:30 AM on October 4th.
interesting points: The object was described as brilliantly lit and appeared to be of a saucer shape, emanating from the outline of the saucer shape.
The object maneuvered over the ocean and was estimated to be about half a mile high.
A bright white vapor trail from the object was visible from the newspaper office and police station, and other observers had called in with the same description.
The observer was shocked by what they saw, as they had never observed anything like it before.
The observer wanted to acquire any additional information available regarding the sighting.
